topComments.text:
Unless it's a student production ALWAYS pay your cast and crew. Start a crowdfunding campaign, apply for grants, take out a personal bank loan, hold bake sales and car washes, meet with local/regional businesses for product placement.

Even Spike Lee, before he was "Spike Lee" got financing for his first film "She's Gotta Have It" when no one even knew who Spike Lee was..But STOP this practice of expecting Actors and Crew to work for free on your films.

What about liability insurance to cover the cast and crew on set? A film set is a place where a lot of incidents could happen. What if they get hurt on set? How are you going to compensate them for their medical expenses and lost work time? How are you going to cover equipment damaged or lost to such a situation? What if the property (house, offices, vase, etc. ) gets damaged, how are you going to cover those expenses?

What about a completion bond to insure the film is finished or pay the people for their time if it's not? Do you have that? 

My point is you have to start treating your business as a BUSINESS and stop expecting cast and crew to work for free. Filmmaking isn't just shooting footage on set and cutting it together in post. Part of filmmaking is finding the funding to make a film. And if you don't want to do that legwork then you don't really want to be in the film industry.

Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies and some kind of Art House Underground Movies. I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.

I wanted to share my gratitude for what was an outstanding holiday season of events, ranging from the local Midas Sign that kick things off this season  to the tree lighting ceremony at the Capitol in Sacramento.

Thank you to the University of California Student and Policy Center for the invitation to their well-stocked reception. The conversation was marvelous‚ÄîI haven't laughed that hard or had such deep conversations that left me wanting more in a long time. I also appreciate the Berkeley Policy Center for their intriguing night of discussion.

Finally, a shout-out to my friends at Sacramento Startup for the fun night at the Urban Hive. It is truly shaping up to be the place for events and gatherings, and I look forward to hosting an event there soon.

Ich bin angehender Hobbyfotograf aus dem Raum Krefeld/D√ºsseldorf und suche Menschen, die Lust auf ein lockeres, unkompliziertes Fotoshooting haben. Vorkenntnisse oder Erfahrung sind nicht n√∂tig ‚Äì wir probieren alles in Ruhe gemeinsam aus, ohne Erwartungen oder Druck.

Den Ort w√§hlen wir zusammen: Park, Wasser, Stadt oder ein Platz, an dem du dich wohlf√ºhlst. Alle Bilder bekommst du in hoher Aufl√∂sung, einige bearbeite ich dezent und nat√ºrlich.

Ich habe au√üerdem eine kleine Portfolio-Seite, die sich noch im Aufbau befindet:
[http://jpegwerkstatt.com/](http://jpegwerkstatt.com/)

Wichtig ist mir ausdr√ºcklich: **Modelma√üe, Figur oder Aussehen spielen f√ºr mich keinerlei Rolle.** Fotografie hat f√ºr mich nichts mit Idealbildern zu tun. Besonders Frauen sollen sich ermutigt f√ºhlen, sich zu zeigen, ohne sich zu sch√§men oder etwas erf√ºllen zu m√ºssen.

Da ich selbst Anf√§nger bin, suche ich **ausschlie√ülich Hobby-Models oder Menschen ohne Erfahrung**, die es einfach ausprobieren m√∂chten. **Profi- oder Agentur-Models bitte nicht anfragen.**

Ich bin im Umkreis von etwa 50‚Äì60 km um Krefeld/D√ºsseldorf mobil.

Bei Interesse freue ich mich √ºber eine Nachricht.üòä

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies and some kind of Art House Underground Movies. I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.

I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch

Thats me

Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 

please ask for details.

items.text:
We are looking for an interested producer to film our comedy Movie "Valley Boys Return" and Our drama movie "Wilbur Street Gangs" and our sitcom "So, You Want to Prank Me, Huh?" Our Valley Boys Return movie is a very funny comical movie about me and my friend growing up in Southern California in the 1970s and 1980s and the very funny comical experience we had happen to us. I believe this comedy movie will be a huge success and we know with everything that has happened in the last five or so years, people need a comical movie to laugh. The other proposals are, "So, You want to Prank me, Huh?" Another funny sitcom show that we would write different shows for it weekly. And the other movie proposal is titled, "The Wilbur Street Gangs" which is more of a drama about my friend and I growing-up in Southern California and the start of the gangs that frequented Southern California and the San Fernando Valley.

We are looking for a producer that will handle the filming of our two movies and sitcom television show, handle working as a team to find funding, (angel investors, etc.) and after our movie is filmed and television shows, get them to Hollywood to make it to the big screen. We will work as a team with our producer on playing parts in our movies and show and consult on set as you are filming and work with our producers team to get our script completely written to turn our movie and shows into Hollywood hits.

We can also work with our interested producer to find investors, angel investors, etc to fund the filming of our two movies and television show if the producer does not have the funding available. The producer should have points of contact they have worked with in the past for funding sources.

Or, if an interested producer wants to buy our movie ideas and sitcom show ideas, we can negotiate a price to sell them to our interested producer.

If you are interested in learning more about our movies and television show, respond back to this Facebook post or Email be directly at (ronanselm35@gmail.com) and we can set-up a time to talk about where I will go over our movies in more detail and our television show. I have all the proposals written for the movies and shows and a very rough draft script written for the "Valley Boys Return" movie which we would like to sit down with your team and finish the script as a team. Send me a good contact email for you and I can send you a copy of each of our proposals if you are interested.

üé≠ CASTING CALL üé≠
Mr Poole (and The Father)
 in "Dr Jekyll and Mr Hyde"
Grove Productions

We‚Äôre seeking an actor to join our touring production as Mr Poole, Dr Jekyll‚Äôs long-serving butler, who witnesses his master‚Äôs terrifying descent. This is a key supporting role with strong emotional scenes. The role also includes a small secondary part, The Father.

‚ú® Blind casting ‚Äì all actors welcome
üó£Ô∏è Working-class / regional accent required

üíº Pay
‚Ä¢ ¬£101 per performance (inc. holiday pay)
‚Ä¢ ¬£15 per hour for rehearsals (inc. holiday pay)

‚ö†Ô∏è Mid-run replacement ‚Äì fast learning essential
üé≠ Small rep company ‚Äì cast help move props/set & assist with get-outs
‚ôø Reasonable adjustments available

üìÖ Auditions: 9 January
üìÖ Rehearsals: 15 & 16 January

üéüÔ∏è Performance Dates:
‚Ä¢ 19 Jan ‚Äì Clevedon School (Bristol)
‚Ä¢ 3 Feb ‚Äì The Crypt (Gloucester)
‚Ä¢ 9/10 Feb (TBC) ‚Äì Hodge Hill (Birmingham)
‚Ä¢ 9 March ‚Äì Blakehay Theatre, Weston-super-Mare
‚Ä¢ 12 March ‚Äì Blakehay Theatre, Weston-super-Mare
‚Ä¢ 16 March ‚Äì Cheltenham Ladies‚Äô College

üì© To apply:
Send your CV + video audition (using the provided Poole extract) to
admin@groveproductions.org
Closing date for application: 5pm 6th January

Poole Extract

Context - Poole has become increasingly concerned about his master, Dr Jekyll, and has gone to Jekyll‚Äôs friend, Utterson, for help. In this scene, Poole has just asked Utterson to listen at the door to his master‚Äôs voice, as Poole believes it is not his master but a different man, or monster.

Poole:
Well, Mr Utterson, you are a hard man to satisfy. But I‚Äôll do it yet. All this last week, he or it or whatever it is that lives in the laboratory, has been crying night and day for some sort of medicine and cannot get it to his mind. It was sometimes his way ‚Äì the master‚Äôs that is ‚Äì to write his orders on a sheet of paper and throw it on the stair. We‚Äôve had nothing else this week back. Nothing but papers, and a closed door, and the very meals left there to be smuggled in when nobody was looking. Well sir, every day, ay, and twice and thrice in the same day, there have been orders and complaints, and I have been sent flying to all the wholesale chemists in town. Every time I brought the stuff back, there would be another paper telling me to return it, because it was not pure, and another order to a different firm. This drug is wanted bitter bad, sir, whatever for.

DM for more info

sharedPost.text:
ANNOUNCING: READING AND AUDITIONS FOR ‚ÄòTHE WELKIN‚Äô BY LUCY KIRKWOOD 

If you're a female actor in Coventry or the surrounding area, you will DEFINITELY want to check out this audition notice.

‚ÄúA mighty play: magnificent in its scope, depth and intricacy‚Ä¶ a wise, funny, richly intelligent and generously ambitious play that asks, as all good history plays do, how far have we really come?‚Äù
Financial Times

The Welkin is an ensemble piece with 13 remarkable female roles ranging from young to elderly, each one a fully-realised human being with her own voice, her own story, her own truth to tell.

If you‚Äôve ever wanted a role that doesn‚Äôt ask you to be the girlfriend, the mother, or the murder victim- but instead asks you to be complicated, contradictory, funny, furious, and utterly real- this is YOUR play.
 
THE WELKIN
by Lucy Kirkwood 

DIRECTOR: Peter Daly-Dickson

PERFORMANCE DATES: 19th-23rd May 2026

READING: Sunday 11th January 2026, 4pm, at Allesley Village Hall, Birmingham Road, Allesley Village, Coventry, CV5 9GX
*Come along for a cup of tea, a biscuit (or two!) and an informal reading of the play. Hearing a play is a different thing altogether to reading it, and you may find it useful in deciding whether to audition. We'd love to welcome you.

AUDITIONS: Sunday 18th January 2026, 2pm, at Allesley Village Hall, Birmingham Road, Allesley Village, Coventry, CV5 9GX

REHEARSALS: will start on Monday 23rd February 2026 (Every Monday and Thursday 7:30pm)

Please contact Peter Daly-Dickson should you have any questions about the production or to register your interest:
hello@saintsdramacoventry.org

‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶‚Ä¶
THE PLAY
The year is 1759. A child has been murdered. The accused, 21-year-old Sally Poppy, must convince twelve matrons that she is pregnant to spare herself from the gallows.

But these women - midwives, shopkeepers, servants, a colonel‚Äôs widow - have their own secrets, their own grief, their own rage at the world that uses them and ignores them in equal measure.

Locked in a room together, they must decide: Will they save Sally? Can they trust her? And what power do they really hold when the verdict is already written by men?

Written by Lucy Kirkwood, 'The Welkin' premiered at the National Theatre in 2020 to critical acclaim and is theatre that crackles with dark wit and raw humanity - a 'beautiful, weird, horror' story about women judging women, about mercy and motherhood, housework and murder, and what happens when the powerless are suddenly given the power of life and death.

'The Welkin' is an ensemble piece with 13 remarkable female roles ranging from young to elderly, each one a fully-realised human being with her own voice, her own story, her own truth to tell.

THE CHARACTERS TO BE CAST:

THE ACCUSED
SALLY POPPY, the murderer, twenty-one years old or thereabouts

THE JURY OF 12 MATRONS - All actors cast for the jury of matrons must look old enough to have had experience of childbirth
ELIZABETH (LIZZY) LUKE, the midwife, thirty-five years old, give or take

And
JUDITH BREWER, older
CHARLOTTE CARY, older
KITTY GIVENS, young, Scottish accent
HELEN LUDLOW, middle-aged
SARAH HOLLIS, middle-aged, older than Lizzy
EMMA JENKINS, middle-aged
ANN LAVENDER, young
MARY MIDDLETON, young, will be made to look pregnant
HANNAH RUSTED, young
SARAH SMITH, older
PEG CARTER, young, will be made to look pregnant

And Also
MR COOMBES, the bailiff 

FREDERICK POPPY, the husband
MR WILLIS, the doctor 
(These two roles possibly played by the same actor) 

KATY LUKE, the midwife‚Äôs daughter
ALICE WAX, the child victim
(Possibly played by the same actor) 

LADY WAX, the mother of the victim

items.text:
I am currently Producing a brand new show for Channel 4 in creating an alternative court to resolve your disputes, without the usual costs and delays.

Has a dispute got out of hand?

Do you want to draw a line under a conflict that‚Äôs been going on too long?

In this brand-new series, from the makers of *Long Lost Family,* we‚Äôll open the doors of a fast-track court that will help people settle their civil disputes.

All those who take part will be provided with **free expert legal representation**.

**We are looking for people who would like to sort out a dispute in a swift and legally-binding hearing.**

Why should you take part?
* Do you feel that you are owed money, an apology, or simply justice on a matter?
Perhaps you want a refund on a service you paid for? Maybe you feel an ex-partner or family member has taken more than their fair share? Whatever the issue, big or small, this could be your chance to have your story heard and to reach a final verdict.
* Perhaps the civil court system feels too complex, too costly, or just takes too long.
* Perhaps you‚Äôd like the free advice of some of Britain‚Äôs top lawyers (likely in region of ¬£10,000)

**If you want to apply or have a no obligation conversation with someone to find out more then drop me a message**

**PAID OPPORTUNITY ‚Äì Origin Originals**

üì¢ Calling all women with extraordinary true stories!

We‚Äôre launching a brand-new series for Origin (650k+), the platform where **women share their most intimate, powerful, and unforgettable real-life experiences.**

We're looking for women with extraordinary true stories: parenting, disability, sexuality, addiction, and beyond. If your story is shocking, unforgettable, or something people won't believe, we want to share it.

If that sounds like you (or someone you know), get in touch!

üá¨üáß You must be based in the UK to apply.

üé• This is a** paid opportunity** and filming happens in a** London** studio.

üìß Send your video tape submission to: **[mireille.lee@upstream-media.co.uk](mailto:mireille.lee@upstream-media.co.uk)**

‚úÖ 1-PAGE PRESS SHEET (MEDIA / BOOKSTORES / PROMO)

---

BOOK PRESS SHEET

Title:
A Journey n Life of the CEO (AMC Worldwide)

Author:
Anthony ‚ÄúAntCeo‚Äù Conley

Publisher:
AMC Records LLC

Genre:
Biography / Memoir / Business & Entrepreneurship

Tagline:
A True Story of Grit, Faith, and Global Vision ‚Äî From the Streets to CEO

---

Overview

A Journey n Life of the CEO (AMC Worldwide) is a powerful memoir chronicling the rise of entrepreneur and media executive Anthony ‚ÄúAntCeo‚Äù Conley, founder of AMC Worldwide. Through 16 chapters and a compelling epilogue, Conley shares his unfiltered journey from hardship and systemic obstacles to building a global multimedia brand.

Blending raw life experience with executive-level insight, the book offers readers a rare look at leadership, ownership, resilience, and faith‚Äîwithout shortcuts or industry privilege.

---

Key Themes

Entrepreneurship from the ground up

Leadership through adversity

Ownership, branding, and discipline

Faith, resilience, and second chances

---

Why This Book Matters

Unlike polished corporate success stories, this memoir delivers real-world lessons for entrepreneurs, creatives, and leaders navigating today‚Äôs economic and cultural realities.

---

Formats

Print (Paperback / Hardcover)

Digital (Kindle / ePub)

Audiobook (In Production)

---

Author Bio

Anthony ‚ÄúAntCeo‚Äù Conley is the founder and CEO of AMC Worldwide, a multimedia company spanning music, film, podcasting, and digital distribution. Known for his authentic leadership and commitment to ownership and empowerment, Conley uses his platform to uplift underrepresented voices and create sustainable opportunities.

---

Press & Media Contact

üìß amcrecordstv@gmail.com
üìß amcworldmusic7@gmail.com

üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äì STUDENT SHORT FILM üé¨

**UNPAID**

Hey everyone! I‚Äôm currently casting for my upcoming short film, *After the Rain*, an intimate emotional drama about two sisters navigating the aftermath of their mother‚Äôs sudden death. When a violent storm forces Mia and Isla back together, unspoken grief and buried pain rise to the surface, pushing them toward understanding, healing, and renewed connection.

To be shot in: High Wycombe/ London 

**Synopsis:**

After their mother‚Äôs sudden death, two sisters are pulled apart by grief, distance, and unspoken pain. Mia, the older sister, leaves to pursue a promising job opportunity, trying to outrun the heartbreak of their loss. Isla stays behind, sinking into isolation and self-destructive behaviour as her distress deepens. When Mia returns on a stormy night to find Isla drunk and unravelling, the sisters are forced to confront years of buried resentment and abandonment. Through raw confessions and shared vulnerability, they begin a journey towards understanding, forgiveness, and the possibility of hope, finding solace in the quiet strength of sisterhood. 

Characters:

**ISLA (19-22, FEMALE)** 

impulsive, reckless, emotionally unstable little sister. Must be able to portray internal conflict and intoxication.  

**MIA (25-28, FEMALE)**

protective, compassionate, responsible older sister. Must be able to portray internal conflict and the effects of grief. 

Shooting: DATES TBC  (approx JAN 6-16th)    

If interested, please contact me for more information at austenfilmworks@gmail.com 

Please feel free to share or tag anyone who might be interested. üé•üé¨

We are seeking strong, talented comedic actors for our production of 'YOU CAN'T TAKE IT WITH YOU'. These are non-equity auditions by appointment. All roles are volunteer. No housing or pay will be provided. 

AUDITION DATES:  
- Monday, February 2nd, 6:00pm-10:00pm
- Tuesday, February 3rd, 6:00pm-10:00pm
*Auditions will consist of monologues and cold reading.

LOCATION: Delray Beach Playhouse (Delray Beach, FL) 

PREPARATION: 
-Please prepare a short comedic monologue.
-Actors may also be asked to do cold reads (sides will be provided).

In lieu of attending in-person auditions, VIDEO SUBMISSIONS WILL BE ACCEPTED ‚Äì Deadline for submission is January 29 at 9:00pm. 

VIDEO PREPARATION:
- Please slate your name and confirm your location.
- please tape a 1-minute comedic monologue.
*Due by 9pm, Jan. 29th

Full Audition Breakdown here: [https://auditionsmanager.com/registration.php?AU=v10HYL1698](https://auditionsmanager.com/registration.php?AU=v10HYL1698)

CASTING CALL ‚Äì STUDENT ACTING REEL PROJECT
We are seeking five actors for a student-led project creating professionally shot scenes for acting showreels.
Roles:
4 x Male
1 x Female
Playing age: 18‚Äì26
Production Details:
Location: Leeds
Shoot dates: Between 28 December ‚Äì 2 January
Actors will likely be required for one shooting day only, as each scene will be approximately one minute in length.
Scripts have been prepared and will be provided upon confirmation.
Payment:
This is an unpaid student project intended for showreel material.
Submissions:
If interested, please submit via email to shivamchawala12@gmail.com with:
Headshot
CV (if available)
Showreel link (if available)
Suitable applicants will be contacted with further details.

**CASTING CALL: THREE ACTOR-SINGERS FOR RECURRING MUSICAL COMEDY PROJECT **

**Project Title:** Standing On Shoulders 

**Production Company:** Independent 

**Casting Director:** Adam Scamvougeras 

**Union Status:** Non-Union 

**Compensation:** Credit & Footage Provided 

What if The Beatles were socially inept or The Monkees were morally corrupt? You get Standing On Shoulders! This project is an original musical comedy project that mixes narrative storytelling with humorous songs, performed by a recurring ensemble.

We are seeking three actor-singers to complete the four-person performance group.  

This particular project is acting-first. Actors should have strong comedic instincts and solid singing abilities. Instrumental ability is seen as a plus but not required. The music itself is created in collaboration with talented musicians from Vancouver and abroad.

While this project is ongoing, it is not a full-time commitment. Scheduling is flexible and performers will have plenty of time for other acting opportunities. This is a collaborative, passion-driven project designed to grow over time.

In 2026, we will be creating a few musical comedy videos. The long-term ambition with this project is to make albums or features starring the band. 

This is a recurring project for actors interested in returning to the same project over time. 

The available roles are as follows:

BAND MEMBER #1 (Male, mid-late 20s, open ethnicity) The ‚Äúsuave‚Äù one. His motivation for being part of the band is to meet girls. 

BAND MEMBER #2 (Male, mid-late 20s, open ethnicity) The ‚Äúpunk‚Äù one. His motivation for being part of the band is as a chance to rebel against the entertainment industry. 

BAND MEMBER #3 (Female, mid-late 20s, open ethnicity) The ‚Äúambitious‚Äù one. Her motivation for being part of the band is to get noticed. She sees the band as a stepping stone to better things and is always one foot out the door. 

For submissions, please submit a headshot, a resume (if available), and two short videos (30-60 seconds each): 

1) Singing sample

2) Acting sample for the role you're submitting for. It can be a brief monologue, a conversation with your friend, a self-written bit, etc. 

Please email to adamscamvougeras@gmail.com. Also, please include a brief message in the email explaining why you feel you‚Äôre right for the project and what interests you about it. 

Thank you so much for taking the time to consider my project, and I** **wish you all the happiest of holidays.

## CASTING CALL ‚Äî AMBER (LEAD rOLE)

**Project: Short Film**

Genre: Psychological Drama / Tech Thriller

Shoot Location: Lower Mainland, BC

Shoot Dates: TBD

Compensation: Volunteer / Passion Project

**ROLE: AMBER**

Age Range: 27‚Äì40

Gender: Female

Ethnicity: Open / Race-agnostic

**CHARACTER SNAPSHOT**

Amber is a high-performing Director of Sales at a tech company. Outwardly confident and disciplined, she is internally restless and unable to feel content. She is addicted to the chase‚Äîalways moving forward, never celebrating wins.

When Amber gains access to an experimental technology, she relies on it too much. The technology destabilizes her judgment, blurring truth, error, and perception.

By the end, she withdraws from modern life‚Äînot in rebellion, but to preserve her sanity.

**PERFORMANCE NOTES**

This is a subtle, internal performance. We are seeking an actor who can convey psychological shifts through restraint, stillness, and micro-expression.

This is not a loud breakdown. Amber‚Äôs collapse is quiet, logical, and unsettling‚Äîdriven by over-certainty and loss of trust in her own judgment.

**KEY TRAITS**

Intelligent

Controlled

Ambitious (not arrogant)

Emotionally guarded

Increasingly detached

**AUDITION REQUIREMENTS**

Self-tape audition

One dramatic scene (sides to be provided)

**SUBMISSION DETAILS**

Please submit:

Headshot

Resume (if available)

Email submissions to: soultales.ca@gmail.com

Subject: AMBER ‚Äì Casting Submission

**NOTE!!!**

This is a serious passion project with a small, committed team. We are looking for actors who are reliable, prepared, and respectful of time and effort. Please apply only if you can fully commit to rehearsals, shoot days, and clear communication throughout the process. Consistency and follow-through are essential for this role.

This project is not suitable for flaky or tentative participation. If you are unsure about your availability or commitment, we kindly ask that you do not apply.

items.text:
This is a question for all sag union people out there. Originally our feature film untethered we wanted make a sag film but after talking to my EP he recommended that we book a sag E actress and currently we are talking to on.

My question is under sag aftra rules what are the requirements for sag Eligible contracts, when it comes down to payment and per day?

topComments.text:
Hi Tyler. SAG-AFTRA Actor and signatory producer here. You‚Äôre getting some incomplete answers. Basically it comes down to whether or not you decided to make your project under a SAG-AFTRA contract or not.  And pay requirements depend on the type of SAG-AFTRA contract you decided to use for your project. It has nothing to do with the union eligibility of one of the actors. 

Most of the people on this thread are correct about the SAG eligible Actor. SAG eligible means they are still non-union. They are eligible to join the union, but have not yet done so. So if your project is not being made under a SAG-AFTRA contract, they are still allowed to work your project, and there are no considerations you have to worry about in regard to the union. However, no SAG-AFTRA MEMBER actors may work on your nonunion project. 

This is where a lot of your answers are incomplete. If you did your project in a SAG-AFTRA contract, depending on the type of contract, you may or may not have to pay your actors at all. Even if they are SAG-AFTRA members. However, doing your project under a SAG contract will allow SAG-AFTRA members to act in your project. Contracts like SAG micro budget, SAG student, SAG Indie, and SAG ultra low budget all have ways of allowing for ultra low budget projects to do things like defer pay or no pay for actors. Even if they are full members of the union. But if you make your project a SAG-AFTRA contract project, then ALL actors in the project are covered and protected by SAG-AFTRA rules. This means that if you had budgeted a pay rate for actors, then all actors whether they are union members or not, would be subject to the same pay scale. Whether that is no pay, $150 a day, or $1000 a day. SAG-AFTRA contracts are not about treating some actors better than others. They are about making sure that all actors are protected, treated fairly, and paid fairly and most important transparently.

So if I am understanding correctly, you have a non-union project, that has employed a SAG-AFTRA eligible Actor. In this case, you have absolutely no requirements regarding the union. This is because your project is not being made under a SAG-AFTRA agreement.  the rules are about your project status. Not about the Actor‚Äôs eligibility status.
There are no requirements. They are not yet full union members, so they can still work on non-union projects without restrictions.

The Ghost That Could- Casting Call/Updates

Grateful the project was recently awarded the: @fromtheheartproductions ‚ÄòHot Film In The Making Roy W. Dean Grant FALL 2025‚Äô laurel

Excited to be moving into the test shoots stage of production in coming months(Jan-April). I went ahead and emailed some self tape request to those who expressed serious interest via email-

To anyone who responded before who is still interested in being part of the team/actor email: mattiemacaya@gmail.com with a resume and area of skill, attach resume

For self tapes please follow below instructions: 

For this stage, we would love to see a short, silent self-tape that gives us a sense of your emotional range and presence. No monologue is needed. 

Please submit this by NO LATER then end of dayJanuary 17 2026. For anyone interested in production assisting/marketing/makeup/etc email NO LATER then end of day January 20 2026.

What to include:

* Film either inside or outside ‚Äî whatever feels most comfortable and natural to you
* Keep the framing horizontal
* A simple moment where you move through an emotion or emotional shift (this can be very subtle)30seconds to 1 minute. 
* Please include a brief slate at the end with your name

After the slate, please answer the following two questions on camera (casually ‚Äî no need to overthink):

1. When do you feel most like yourself?
2. What‚Äôs something you notice about people that others often miss?

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

Shoot Details: 

Test Shoot for Film Short

Non-union

Shoot Dates: TBD January - April 2026

Rate of Pay: Food/Beverage provided

Location: Denver, CO and surrounding locations

Side note from the üëª : if you‚Äôre submitting note the team will not respond to direct PMs on here nor will anyone chase you down for follow up if you are selected- that is ON YOU. Meet the self tape/application deadline if you‚Äòre serious and can commit, there can only be ONE ghost on this project everyone else will have to haunt elsewhere.

Thank you all for continued interest and support! Let‚Äôs collaborate on some magical storytelling in the new year and get this on 2026-2027 Festival Circuit.

Setgefl√ºster 4: "Darsteller Seele, nutzt Du Schmerz als Rolle?" 

In diesem Teil wird deutlich, warum Setgefl√ºster mehr ist als ein Blick hinter die Kulissen. Wir sprechen nicht nur √ºber Drehtage, Abl√§ufe und typische Set-Momente, sondern √ºber das, was Darsteller wirklich mitbringen, ihren inneren Kern. Denn auch wenn jemand vor der Kamera souver√§n wirkt, bedeutet das nicht, dass innen alles leicht ist. 

Der Einstieg f√ºhlt sich erst nach lockerer Pause an, kurze Begr√º√üung, ein bisschen Set-Alltag, dieses Gef√ºhl von, wir reden einfach. Und dann kippt es in eine Situation, die viele kennen, aber kaum jemand anspricht: Narben werden sichtbar. 

Genau hier passiert etwas Wichtiges: Wir zeigen, wie man N√§he nicht durch Schweigen baut, sondern durch Haltung. Denn Respekt ist nicht, so zu tun als w√§re nichts da. Respekt ist, den Menschen zu sehen und die richtige Form zu finden. Im Gespr√§ch wird klar, dass es einen Unterschied gibt zwischen Starren und ehrlicher Neugier, zwischen Voyeurismus und Verbindung. 

Dann wird es konkret, weil wir nicht nur √ºber Narben als Symbol sprechen, sondern √ºber Narben als medizinisches Thema. Es f√§llt der Begriff Keloidnarben, dazu hypertrophe Narben, und sogar die Info, dass es unterschiedliche Auspr√§gungen geben kann. 

Was Setgefl√ºster Teil 4 besonders macht, ist die n√§chste Ebene: Intimit√§t und Selbstwert. Wir sprechen dar√ºber, was es bedeutet, wenn man seinen K√∂rper nicht einfach neutral erlebt, sondern als etwas, das bewertet wird. Da geht es um Licht, das man lieber ausmacht. 

Und hier kommt der Br√ºckenschlag zur Schauspielerei: Eine Rolle verlangt Pr√§senz. Pr√§senz bedeutet, Du bist da, mit K√∂rper, Stimme, Blick, Atmung. 

Zu mir, Christian Wei√üe 

Ich bin Christian Wei√üe, Medienunternehmer, Content Creator und Inhaber der Karrideo Image- und Eventfilmproduktion aus K√∂ln. Ich entwickle Bewegtbildformate, erz√§hle Geschichten f√ºr Unternehmen,Organisationen und Pers√∂nlichkeiten und kenne als Darsteller beide Seiten der Kamera. 

Wie w√ºrdest Du wollen, dass man Dich auf etwas Sichtbares an Deinem K√∂rper anspricht, damit es sich respektvoll anf√ºhlt? 

Gef√§llt dir das Video, dann abonniere den Kanal, aktiviere die Glocke, gib dem Video einen Daumen nach oben, schreib Deine Sicht in die Kommentare und besuche mind_body_coach_ auf Instagram f√ºr weitere Impulse. 

Christian Wei√üe aka @christian_ugc_creator

message.text: Grateful beyond words for all my family and friends who became part of my 2025 journey. Thank you for the love, support, and memories that carried me through the highs and lows. To my fellow men and everyone facing hardships in life, may we grow stronger, wiser, and more resilient despite the challenges. As we welcome 2026, I pray for healing, hope, and a better year ahead for all of us. üôè‚ú®

Ob Konzerte, Galas, Events oder festliche Anl√§sse ‚Äì ich biete Ihnen eine vielseitige, musikalisch hochwertige Gestaltung, die Ihre Veranstaltung zu einem unvergesslichen Erlebnis macht.

For this reason, Travel On Set  opens the selection process for film industry professionals who wish to join an **international educational program based in New York ‚Äì Queens

We are looking for professionals who are not only highly skilled, but also capable of inspiring, mentoring, and communicating the craft of cinema with passion, ethics, and responsibility.

üé• REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS

Curricula will be evaluated with priority given to candidates who demonstrate:

A dynamic and proactive professional profile

Strong empathy and interpersonal skills

A natural aptitude for teaching and teamwork

Proven professional experience in the film industry

Possession of the Virtus Certificate (mandatory requirement to teach at our school)

‚û°Ô∏è Selected candidates will be able to obtain the Virtus Certificate free of charge, as an integral part of the onboarding and training process within the Travel On Set educational program.

United States

üïí Time:3:00 PM ‚Äì 5:00 PM

üí∞ Compensation: USD 50/hour ‚Äì paid position

‚ú® Travel On Set is more than a training program ‚Äî it is an educational mission at the heart of the international film industry.

If you believe in the power of education, the value of experience, and the responsibility that comes with talent, this project is for you.

items.text:
Hi everyone. This is future-facing, not an immediate ask.

I‚Äôm a director developing my first feature. My first completed screenplay turned out to be the kind of project that, if I‚Äôm fortunate, may represent a culmination rather than a starting point, so I‚Äôm thinking long term and realistically.

The project is an independent, non-studio film. It is a deportation story set in Honduras and designed to be roughly three hours. I‚Äôm fully aware this is not industry friendly or something a studio would buy, and that is intentional. This is a passion project I expect to finance independently if it ever happens.

I‚Äôm not looking for script feedback.

What I‚Äôm trying to do is educate myself years in advance.

For those of you who have worked on or around independent features, especially international or location-heavy productions, I would appreciate insight on practical difficulties you encountered, mistakes you wish you had planned for earlier, insurance or legal considerations I should be aware of, and logistical challenges that often get underestimated.

I am actively working on smaller and more practical projects to build toward this, but I want to understand the realities ahead of time so I‚Äôm not na√Øve about what it takes.

Any experience-based advice is appreciated. Thank you for reading.

‚ú® CASTING CALL ‚Äì A PLACE NOT MINE (CABARET MUSICAL) ‚ú®

Do you want to be part of something special next summer?

Are you looking for a creative project that helps you grow as a performer, collaborate with other artists, and build your portfolio?

We‚Äôre casting for A Place Not Mine, an original cabaret musical inspired by real-life experiences of the writer, reimagined in a magical world influenced by shows like Wicked and contemporary musical theatre.

A story about belonging, identity, love, and finding your voice.

We are looking for London-based actors / actor-singers who are excited to collaborate and tell meaningful stories together.

üé≠ Roles available:

Riven ¬∑ Seraphine ¬∑ Mirra ¬∑ Selene ¬∑ Aurora ¬∑ Oris ¬∑ Vespera ¬∑ Sylas ¬∑ Rowan

üåø Please note:

The role of Riven includes emotional closeness and light intimacy with the main character (male). We are looking for performers who feel comfortable exploring this as part of the story.

üìå Project information:

This is an unpaid project, created as a development / showcase production, with the aim of presenting the work in a professional theatre setting.

The project will offer:

‚Ä¢ Professional performance credit

‚Ä¢ Showreel / recorded footage of the final performance

‚Ä¢ A collaborative, supportive rehearsal process

üìÜ Availability:

Rehearsals expected to take place between March/April‚Äì July, with performances planned for July/August. (exact dates TBC).

üì© How to audition:

Please send:

‚Ä¢ CV

‚Ä¢ Showreel or self-tape

‚Ä¢ Two singing videos (one musical theatre song + one song of your choice)

to: üëâ emilvasilev296@gmail.com, just add the name of the character you're applying for. 

(Feel free to reach out with any questions!)

If this feels like a project you‚Äôd enjoy, we‚Äôd truly love to hear from you üíõ

Setgefl√ºster 4: "Darsteller Seele, nutzt Du Schmerz als Rolle?" 

In diesem Teil wird deutlich, warum Setgefl√ºster mehr ist als ein Blick hinter die Kulissen. Wir sprechen nicht nur √ºber Drehtage, Abl√§ufe und typische Set-Momente, sondern √ºber das, was Darsteller wirklich mitbringen, ihren inneren Kern. Denn auch wenn jemand vor der Kamera souver√§n wirkt, bedeutet das nicht, dass innen alles leicht ist. 

Der Einstieg f√ºhlt sich erst nach lockerer Pause an, kurze Begr√º√üung, ein bisschen Set-Alltag, dieses Gef√ºhl von, wir reden einfach. Und dann kippt es in eine Situation, die viele kennen, aber kaum jemand anspricht: Narben werden sichtbar. 

Genau hier passiert etwas Wichtiges: Wir zeigen, wie man N√§he nicht durch Schweigen baut, sondern durch Haltung. Denn Respekt ist nicht, so zu tun als w√§re nichts da. Respekt ist, den Menschen zu sehen und die richtige Form zu finden. Im Gespr√§ch wird klar, dass es einen Unterschied gibt zwischen Starren und ehrlicher Neugier, zwischen Voyeurismus und Verbindung. 

Dann wird es konkret, weil wir nicht nur √ºber Narben als Symbol sprechen, sondern √ºber Narben als medizinisches Thema. Es f√§llt der Begriff Keloidnarben, dazu hypertrophe Narben, und sogar die Info, dass es unterschiedliche Auspr√§gungen geben kann. 

Was Setgefl√ºster Teil 4 besonders macht, ist die n√§chste Ebene: Intimit√§t und Selbstwert. Wir sprechen dar√ºber, was es bedeutet, wenn man seinen K√∂rper nicht einfach neutral erlebt, sondern als etwas, das bewertet wird. Da geht es um Licht, das man lieber ausmacht. 

Und hier kommt der Br√ºckenschlag zur Schauspielerei: Eine Rolle verlangt Pr√§senz. Pr√§senz bedeutet, Du bist da, mit K√∂rper, Stimme, Blick, Atmung. 

Zu mir, Christian Wei√üe 

Ich bin Christian Wei√üe, Medienunternehmer, Content Creator und Inhaber der Karrideo Image- und Eventfilmproduktion aus K√∂ln. Ich entwickle Bewegtbildformate, erz√§hle Geschichten f√ºr Unternehmen,Organisationen und Pers√∂nlichkeiten und kenne als Darsteller beide Seiten der Kamera. 

Wie w√ºrdest Du wollen, dass man Dich auf etwas Sichtbares an Deinem K√∂rper anspricht, damit es sich respektvoll anf√ºhlt? 

Gef√§llt dir das Video, dann abonniere den Kanal, aktiviere die Glocke, gib dem Video einen Daumen nach oben, schreib Deine Sicht in die Kommentare und besuche mind_body_coach_ auf Instagram f√ºr weitere Impulse. 

Christian Wei√üe aka @christian_ugc_creator

Stanislavski vs Meisner - Which Technique Is Right for You?

Every actor eventually asks this question:
**Do I build from the inside out‚Äîor live in the moment?**

Stanislavski and Meisner are two of the most influential acting techniques ever created‚Äîbut they train very different muscles.

One focuses on *inner truth.*
The other on *real-time reaction.*

Understanding the difference can change your entire approach to acting.

üëâ Learn the full breakdown at **cineconnectstagecraft.org**

Actors often think auditions are about impressing. Casting Directors are actually looking for clarity, professionalism, and trust.
Every audition silently answers three questions:

Can you take direction?
Can we work with you?
When you understand that, your auditions change completely.

We are casting for an updated tour of the children‚Äôs theatre show, ‚ÄúThe Dinosaur That Pooped a Rock Show‚Äù, based on the popular books by McFly‚Äôs Tom Fletcher and Dougie Poynter. 

The show is written and directed by Miranda Larson with songs and music by Tom Fletcher & Dougie Poynter and Barrie Bignold and is produced by Mark Thompson at MT Productions. 

**Production dates:**

Auditions will take place on 24th November 2025

Rehearsals begin on 12th January ‚Äì 22nd January 2026 in London
Tour dates Jan ‚Äì Nov 2026.
We are currently have 91 dates and counting. 

**Production location: **Greater London

**Role: **We are looking for a costume character/ skin artist to play the role of Dino. The artist will need to operate Dino‚Äôs mouth, hands and head, bringing the character to life. They will also be required to join in dance moves and routines whilst inside the costume. We are looking for someone between 5‚Äô6‚Äù and 5‚Äô10‚Äù tall. Previous skin/ costume character experience is essential.

The successful applicant will need to have a full UK drivers licence and will be comfortable driving the touring van on a shared basis with the rest of the company.

Please send CV's & headshots to: casting.mtproductions@gmail.com

**Fees:**

Rehearsal fee: ¬£550pw

Show day fee: ¬£150

Travel day fee: ¬£50

Subsistence: ¬£20

AUDITONS FOR RAG DOLLY - THE RAGGEDY ANN MUSICAL WORKSHOP 

Seeking actors for a public workshop reading of Rag Dolly. Come aboard our cast and our bed-boat as we sail through Mexico up to LA to cure a broken heart! Look for actors, singers, dancers, non singers and youth actors. 

RAGGEDY ANN WANTS YOU TO AUDITION!

In Rag Dolly, a little girl named Marcella is dying of a mysterious illness. Her father makes her a rag doll to comfort her, and his stories of the doll come to life in her dreams to guide her through her grief and fear. Marcella and her new friends confront wolves, witches, and incompetent doctors on their way to outwit death and mend her broken heart.

üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äì SHORT FILM (UK) üé¨

Title: INTELLIGENCE UNLEASHED
Genre: Thriller / Crime / Revenge
Shoot Location: UK (North England ‚Äì Manchester area preferred)
Shoot Dates: TBC (Approx. 4 days)
Format: Short Film (Festival-focused)

Paid: No.
Scene showreel footage provided. Opportunity for international festival exposure and visibility to film academies.
üéñ If any cast member wins Best Actor at a festival, ¬£700 will be awarded by the production.

We are casting for an intense, character-driven short film exploring grief, intelligence, crime, and revenge. We are looking for committed actors comfortable with emotionally demanding material.

üé≠ ROLES AVAILABLE
ETHAN CROSS (18‚Äì20) ‚Äì MALE

Lead Role

A brilliant, introverted young programmer whose life is shattered by his father‚Äôs murder. Emotionally layered: grief, restraint, intelligence, and controlled rage. Must convincingly play quiet intensity and emotional transitions.

Key traits: Intelligent, reserved, emotionally deep, dangerous when pushed
Scenes include: Emotional drama, intense solo moments
Accent: Any neutral UK accent

THERON CROSS (40s) ‚Äì MALE

Supporting Role

Ethan‚Äôs father. A loving family man hiding a dangerous past. Warm, protective, conflicted. Appears in family scenes and flashbacks.

Key traits: Charismatic, protective, morally conflicted
Scenes include: Family drama, crime confrontation

EVELYN CROSS (40s) ‚Äì FEMALE

Supporting Role

Ethan‚Äôs mother. Strong, loving, emotionally shattered by loss. Must handle raw grief and intimate emotional scenes.

Key traits: Warm, resilient, emotionally powerful
Scenes include: Grief, emotional dialogue

GORGOS (Late 40s‚Äì50s) ‚Äì MALE

Antagonist

Cold, intelligent criminal mastermind. Calm, intimidating, and charismatic. Believes in control, loyalty, and eliminating loose ends.

Key traits: Menacing calm, authority, intelligence
Scenes include: Threatening dialogue, criminal negotiations
Accent: Open (UK / European welcome)

THE ASSASSIN (30s‚Äì40s) ‚Äì MALE

Supporting Role

Professional hitman. Silent, controlled, predatory. Minimal dialogue but strong physical presence required.

Key traits: Intimidating, disciplined, physical confidence
Scenes include: Weapon handling (prop only), intense confrontation
‚ö† No real firearms used

GORGOS‚Äô RIGHT-HAND MAN (30s‚Äì40s) ‚Äì MALE

Small Supporting Role

Loyal enforcer. Observant, calculating, dangerous.

üé• IMPORTANT NOTES

All weapons are prop / air guns only

Professional insurance & safety protocols in place

Suitable for actors building strong showreel material

IMDb credit provided

üì© TO APPLY

Please send:

Name

Age

Location

Headshot

Showreel (if available)

üìç Subject: INTELLIGENCE UNLEASHED ‚Äì Role
To üìß Email:  roxanne.marie51119@gmail.com

**RUSH CALL!**

**Are you a LARPer, reenactor, or HEMA fighter who already owns armor and just wants to swing a sword on camera?**

Narrowcast Productions and Good Fruit Media are putting together a **rush medieval battle shoot** for a low-budget, proof-of-concept short film titled ***To the Hilt***, and we‚Äôre looking for **knights and foot soldiers** to fill the frame.

**When? January 5****th**** in the afternoon/evening**
**Where? Just north of Bellville, TX (more details upon email)**
**Commitment?** **Approx. 2.5‚Äì3 hours**

**THE DEAL:**

¬∑ Background warriors (no speaking roles)

¬∑ Possible featured extras

¬∑ Swordplay only

¬∑ Non-union

¬∑ **Unpaid passion project** (meal provided *after* the shoot)

**YOU MUST:**

¬∑ Be a male legal adult (18-50s)

¬∑ Bring your **own medieval wardrobe/armor** (1000-1200s-era look)

¬∑ Arrive costume ready. This shoot will move fast.

¬∑ Have safe weapons (props preferred, but bring what you can)

**EXPERIENCE:**
Stage combat, reenactment, Buhurt, HEMA, or SCA experience preferred ‚Äî but if you can fight with a broadsword convincingly, we‚Äôll take it.

**IMPORTANT: **

¬∑ Choreography will be mostly **self-determined** (no pre-rehearsal time)

¬∑ We are not liable for any injuries or damaged equipment. Act accordingly.

¬∑ Some performers may do paired combat

¬∑ Due to location limits, we can only take **18 people max**

 **To submit:**
Send headshot, armor photos, experience (if any), IMDb (optional), and questions to
**narrowcastproductions@gmail.com**

If you‚Äôve ever wanted to look like you stepped out of a medieval chronicle for an afternoon ‚Äî this is your shot.

items.text:
Dieses Jahr haben wir etwas ver√§ndert.

 

Wir haben aufgeh√∂rt, Schauspiel nur √ºber Technik, Wissen und ‚Äûrichtig machen‚Äú zu denken.

 

Wir haben die Casting-Mastermind gestartet ‚Äì mit elf Menschen, die bereit waren f√ºr Pr√§senz statt Performance. Wir haben w√∂chentlich gearbeitet, gefilmt, trainiert, Szenen gebaut, Energiearbeit gemacht und echte Ausstrahlung vor der Kamera entwickelt.

 

Viele von ihnen wurden in Schauspiel- und People-Agenturen aufgenommen, bekamen Rollen, Engagements oder Preise. Nicht weil sie ‚Äûfertig‚Äú waren, sondern weil sie wirkten.

 

Im Oktober waren wir vier Tage lang in Irland. Showrealszenen, Embodiment, Natur, Workshops, Luxus, Stille, Tiefgang. Dort ist klar geworden: Technik reicht nicht. Pr√§senz entscheidet.

 

Damit entstand die Essenz-Methode.

 

Eine Methode aus Schauspiel, Nervensystem, Kamera, Energie und Embodiment ‚Äì in 7 Buchstaben:

E ‚Äì Erleben

S ‚Äì Selbst

S ‚Äì Seele

E ‚Äì Emotion

N ‚Äì N√§he

Z ‚Äì Zwischen den Zeilen

 

2026 werden wir diese Methode weitergeben.

Erster Schritt: **Essenz-Workshop am 10. Januar.**

Live, on Camera, begrenzt, Einstieg in die weitere Zusammenarbeit.

Wenn du den Link m√∂chtest, kommentiere **ESSENZ**.

attachments.ocrText: May be an image of text that says 'CASTFINDER AM 10.01. ESSENZ-WORKSHOP 2025 DAS JAHR, IN DEM SCHAUSPIEL WIRKUNG WURDE. EINFACH KOMMENTIEREN IAUSGEWAHLTETEILNEHMER. 11 AUSGEW√ÑHLTE TEILNEHMER. W√ñCHENTLICHE W√ñCHENTLICHEBEGLEITUNG. BEGLEITUNG. ROLLEN. AGENTUREN. AUSZEICHNUNGEN Die Essenz-Methode entsteht.'

Mr Poole (and The Father)
 in "Dr Jekyll and Mr Hyde"
Grove Productions

Poole:
Well, Mr Utterson, you are a hard man to satisfy. But I‚Äôll do it yet. All this last week, he or it or whatever it is that lives in the laboratory, has been crying night and day for some sort of medicine and cannot get it to his mind. It was sometimes his way ‚Äì the master‚Äôs that is ‚Äì to write his orders on a sheet of paper and throw it on the stair. We‚Äôve had nothing else this week back. Nothing but papers, and a closed door, and the very meals left there to be smuggled in when nobody was looking.
